      "question": "What is a deadlock in an operating system?",
      "options": [
        "A) A situation where a process is waiting for a resource it already holds",
        "B) A situation where two or more processes are blocked indefinitely, each waiting for the other to release a resource",
        "C) A situation where a process is unable to execute due to lack of memory",
        "D) A situation where a process is unable to execute due to a software fault"
